**Why It Happens:**
- Pregnancy hormones keep hair in growth phase
- After birth, all that hair shifts to shedding phase at once
- You're not going bald—you're losing the "extra" hair

**Timeline:**
| Month PP | What to Expect |
|----------|----------------|
| 1-2 | Hair seems normal |
| 3-4 | Shedding starts/peaks |
| 5-6 | Shedding continues |
| 6-9 | Shedding slows |
| 9-12 | Regrowth noticeable |
| 12-18 | Back to normal |

**What Helps:**
- Patience (most important)
- Continue prenatal vitamins
- Protein intake
- Gentle hair handling
- Loose hairstyles
- Biotin (limited evidence but low risk)

**What Doesn't Help:**
- Expensive "hair growth" supplements
- Stressing about it (cortisol worsens it)
- Tight ponytails, heat styling

**When to Worry:**
If shedding continues past 12 months or is patchy, see a dermatologist. Could indicate thyroid issues or other postpartum conditions.

**The Regrowth:**
Those baby hairs around your hairline at 6-12 months? That's your hair coming back. They'll eventually blend in.`,
